If it's too high, the guitar may get caught on you. If it's too low, it will take a lot of power to get around, plus you'll have a very destructively large radius of swinging axe. Without holding a pick, try to throw the guitar over your shoulder, making sure that the strap is resisting the guitar. It may take a few tries to get a feel for the rotation and power needed. Do not try to launch it on your first try. If anything, be light on your first few attempts. This plastic Guitar Hero controller is going to slap you in the back a few times. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you're still not getting it, the trick is to have the guitar pulling against the strap, making the strap rotate around your body. Two examples, a bike chain, and a hula hoop. Surely a bike chain will not work without the proper tension. Now think of a hula hoop. The best way to keep it going around is balancing the speed and force with which it is spun. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

When you feel you have figured how out to complete the spin, hold a pick properly, and try again; after all, you'll be doing these while playing. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Spin-a-Guitar-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
